frontmatter.title: Execution Plans And Join Algorithms
frontmatter.description: MUI is one of the most powerful and popular of the React libraries out there, because it comes prepacked with a lot of controls (let’s face it, nobody wants to build a calendar). The idea behind it is it’s an implementation of Google’s Material Design, and it’s really opinionated in that regard, and herein lies one of its problems: a lot of designers don’t want their application to look like Gmail or Android, they will want a specific look and feel.
